CHAPTER 3: METHODOLOGY

3.1 Research Design
This study employs a developmental research design, focusing on the creation and implementation of a web-based capstone project management system.

3.2 System Development Methodology
The project follows the Agile development methodology with the following phases:
- Planning and Requirements Analysis
- System Design and Architecture
- Development and Implementation
- Testing and Quality Assurance
- Deployment and Maintenance

3.3 Technology Stack
The system will be developed using:
- Backend: Laravel PHP Framework
- Database: MySQL
- Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap
- Version Control: Git
- Development Environment: XAMPP/Laravel Homestead

3.4 System Architecture
The system follows the Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture:
- Model: Database interactions and business logic
- View: User interface and presentation layer
- Controller: Request handling and application flow

3.5 Database Design
The database design includes the following main entities:
- Users (Students, Faculty, Administrators)
- Groups and Team Management
- Milestones and Tasks
- Project Submissions
- Notifications and Communications

3.6 User Interface Design
The user interface focuses on:
- Responsive design for multiple devices
- Intuitive navigation and user experience
- Accessibility and usability standards
- Modern and professional appearance

3.7 Testing Strategy
The testing approach includes:
- Unit testing for individual components
- Integration testing for system modules
- User acceptance testing with stakeholders
- Performance and security testing

